  "body": "https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/blob/eae238417862b4797e36fbff928d906bb9242261/contracts/utils/cryptography/MerkleProof.sol#L28\r\n\r\nIn the normal mode of operation a Merkle proof is passed into a contract by a external party. As such there is little benefit to copying the Merkle proof to memory before invoking `_efficientHash`. Therefore gas may be saved if in this case calldata is used instead of memory for the proof variable. Recommend either modifying the contract or offering a variant that utilizes calldata. ",
